Sapporo Light library v1.0 to simulate GRAPE6 hardware with G80/G92 GPUs.

Testes with CUDA version 3.0

Type 'make' to compile the library (libsapporo.a).
 
This "Light" version of Sapporo is without 
multi-threading support and does not need
C++. This makes it easier to integrate into
fortran codes, but beware, it can only use one
GPU device per application!


If you have further questions, feel free to contact me.

